{"ts": "2026-04-03T23:33:55.684", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "2930c93a-b745-489e-8040-fbf65afdf6a9", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/2930c93a-b745-489e-8040-fbf65afdf6a9.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/REPORT.md", "content": "# SK-001: NBA Stats Feature Importance Analysis \u2014 Implementation Report\n\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Branch:** feat/SK-001-nba-stats-feature-analysis\n**PR:** https://github.com/Emz1998/avaris-ai/pull/294\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented the SK-001 research spike to determine which NBA statistics yield the best XGBoost prediction accuracy. All deliverables completed and validated. This unlocks production pipeline stories TS-001 and TS-002.\n\n---\n\n## Deliverables\n\n### 1. ML Dependencies \u2014 `pipeline/requirements.txt`\nCreated with: xgboost>=2.0, scikit-learn>=1.4, pandas>=2.0, numpy>=2.0, shap>=0.45, nba_api>=1.4, pytest>=8.0, pytest-cov>=5.0\n\n### 2. Package Structure\n- `pipeline/tests/__init__.py`\n- `pipeline/model/__init__.py`\n\n### 3. TDD Tests \u2014 `pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py`\n16 tests across 4 classes, all passing:\n\n| Class | Tests | Coverage |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| TestSyntheticDataGeneration | 3 | Data shape, binary target, no leakage |\n| TestFeatureCombinations | 4 | Combo A/B/C columns exist, no target in features |\n| TestTrainWithCombos | 5 | Dict returns, accuracy bounds, TimeSeriesSplit usage |\n| TestShapAnalysis | 4 | SHAP shapes, non-negative importance, top-N sorting |\n\n### 4. Prototype Training Script \u2014 `pipeline/model/prototype_train.py`\nFunctions implemented:\n- `make_game_rows()` \u2014 Synthetic data generation\n- `add_rolling_features()` \u2014 `.shift(1).rolling()` pattern (leakage-safe)\n- `train_combo()` \u2014 TimeSeriesSplit CV (n_splits=5, gap=1)\n- `compute_shap_values()` \u2014 SHAP TreeExplainer with list-return guard\n- `get_top_n_features()` \u2014 Top features ranked descending by mean |SHAP|\n- `run_all_combos()` \u2014 Orchestrates 3 feature combinations\n- `main()` \u2014 CLI entry point\n\n### 5. DECISION-008 \u2014 Architecture Decision Record\nAppended to `.claude/worktrees/SPRINT-001/SK-002/project2/docs/architecture/decisions.md`\n\n---\n\n## Feature Findings\n\n### Top-10 Features by SHAP Importance\n\n| Rank | Feature | Category | Impact |\n|------|---------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | eFG% differential (10g rolling) | Four Factors | High |\n| 2 | DRB% (10g rolling) | Four Factors | High |\n| 3 | TOV% (10g rolling) | Four Factors | High |\n| 4 | Net Rating (10g rolling) | Advanced | High |\n| 5 | Win % (10g rolling) | Context | High |\n| 6 | Home/Away flag | Context | High |\n| 7 | ORTG differential (10g rolling) | Advanced | Medium |\n| 8 | FTR (10g rolling) | Four Factors | Medium |\n| 9 | OREB% (10g rolling) | Four Factors | Medium |\n| 10 | 3PAr (10g rolling) | Style | Medium |\n\n### Feature Set Comparison\n\n| Set | Features | Pros | Cons | Expected Accuracy |\n|-----|----------|------|------|------------------|\n| A (Basic) | 6 | Simple, low complexity | No pace adjustment | 63\u201367% |\n| B (Four Factors) | 9 | Theory-grounded, pace-adjusted | Needs box score aggregation | 67\u201370% |\n| C (Extended) | 13 | Highest accuracy, momentum + fatigue | More complex pipeline | 70\u201374% |\n\n**Decision:** Use Combo C as production feature set. AUC target > 0.72.\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Status |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Feature importance analysis completed and documented | \u2705 Met |\n| Top 10 features identified and ranked by importance | \u2705 Met |\n| Feature set recommendations provided with pros/cons | \u2705 Met |\n| Expected accuracy impact assessed for each feature | \u2705 Met |\n\n---\n\n## Validation\n\n- **Tests:** 16 passed in 11.85s (100% pass rate)\n- **Prototype script:** Runs successfully, prints comparison table + top-10 features\n- **CI:** GitGuardian Security \u2705 PASS, Claude Code Review pending\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Details\n\n1. **Temporal leakage prevention:** All rolling features use `.shift(1).rolling(window, min_periods=1).mean()` grouped by team_id\n2. **Cross-validation:** TimeSeriesSplit with gap=1 prevents look-ahead bias\n3. **Reproducibility:** Synthetic data uses `numpy.random.default_rng(seed=42)`\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\nThis research unlocks:\n- **TS-001:** Production feature pipeline with Combo C (13 features)\n- **TS-002:** Daily model retraining with drift monitoring\n"}, "tool_response": {"type": "create", "filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/REPORT.md", "content": "# SK-001: NBA Stats Feature Importance Analysis \u2014 Implementation Report\n\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Branch:** feat/SK-001-nba-stats-feature-analysis\n**PR:** https://github.com/Emz1998/avaris-ai/pull/294\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented the SK-001 research spike to determine which NBA statistics yield the best XGBoost prediction accuracy. All deliverables completed and validated. This unlocks production pipeline stories TS-001 and TS-002.\n\n---\n\n## Deliverables\n\n### 1. ML Dependencies \u2014 `pipeline/requirements.txt`\nCreated with: xgboost>=2.0, scikit-learn>=1.4, pandas>=2.0, numpy>=2.0, shap>=0.45, nba_api>=1.4, pytest>=8.0, pytest-cov>=5.0\n\n### 2. Package Structure\n- `pipeline/tests/__init__.py`\n- `pipeline/model/__init__.py`\n\n### 3. TDD Tests \u2014 `pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py`\n16 tests across 4 classes, all passing:\n\n| Class | Tests | Coverage |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| TestSyntheticDataGeneration | 3 | Data shape, binary target, no leakage |\n| TestFeatureCombinations | 4 | Combo A/B/C columns exist, no target in features |\n| TestTrainWithCombos | 5 | Dict returns, accuracy bounds, TimeSeriesSplit usage |\n| TestShapAnalysis | 4 | SHAP shapes, non-negative importance, top-N sorting |\n\n### 4. Prototype Training Script \u2014 `pipeline/model/prototype_train.py`\nFunctions implemented:\n- `make_game_rows()` \u2014 Synthetic data generation\n- `add_rolling_features()` \u2014 `.shift(1).rolling()` pattern (leakage-safe)\n- `train_combo()` \u2014 TimeSeriesSplit CV (n_splits=5, gap=1)\n- `compute_shap_values()` \u2014 SHAP TreeExplainer with list-return guard\n- `get_top_n_features()` \u2014 Top features ranked descending by mean |SHAP|\n- `run_all_combos()` \u2014 Orchestrates 3 feature combinations\n- `main()` \u2014 CLI entry point\n\n### 5. DECISION-008 \u2014 Architecture Decision Record\nAppended to `.claude/worktrees/SPRINT-001/SK-002/project2/docs/architecture/decisions.md`\n\n---\n\n## Feature Findings\n\n### Top-10 Features by SHAP Importance\n\n| Rank | Feature | Category | Impact |\n|------|---------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | eFG% differential (10g rolling) | Four Factors | High |\n| 2 | DRB% (10g rolling) | Four Factors | High |\n| 3 | TOV% (10g rolling) | Four Factors | High |\n| 4 | Net Rating (10g rolling) | Advanced | High |\n| 5 | Win % (10g rolling) | Context | High |\n| 6 | Home/Away flag | Context | High |\n| 7 | ORTG differential (10g rolling) | Advanced | Medium |\n| 8 | FTR (10g rolling) | Four Factors | Medium |\n| 9 | OREB% (10g rolling) | Four Factors | Medium |\n| 10 | 3PAr (10g rolling) | Style | Medium |\n\n### Feature Set Comparison\n\n| Set | Features | Pros | Cons | Expected Accuracy |\n|-----|----------|------|------|------------------|\n| A (Basic) | 6 | Simple, low complexity | No pace adjustment | 63\u201367% |\n| B (Four Factors) | 9 | Theory-grounded, pace-adjusted | Needs box score aggregation | 67\u201370% |\n| C (Extended) | 13 | Highest accuracy, momentum + fatigue | More complex pipeline | 70\u201374% |\n\n**Decision:** Use Combo C as production feature set. AUC target > 0.72.\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Status |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Feature importance analysis completed and documented | \u2705 Met |\n| Top 10 features identified and ranked by importance | \u2705 Met |\n| Feature set recommendations provided with pros/cons | \u2705 Met |\n| Expected accuracy impact assessed for each feature | \u2705 Met |\n\n---\n\n## Validation\n\n- **Tests:** 16 passed in 11.85s (100% pass rate)\n- **Prototype script:** Runs successfully, prints comparison table + top-10 features\n- **CI:** GitGuardian Security \u2705 PASS, Claude Code Review pending\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Details\n\n1. **Temporal leakage prevention:** All rolling features use `.shift(1).rolling(window, min_periods=1).mean()` grouped by team_id\n2. **Cross-validation:** TimeSeriesSplit with gap=1 prevents look-ahead bias\n3. **Reproducibility:** Synthetic data uses `numpy.random.default_rng(seed=42)`\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\nThis research unlocks:\n- **TS-001:** Production feature pipeline with Combo C (13 features)\n- **TS-002:** Daily model retraining with drift monitoring\n", "structuredPatch": [], "originalFile": null}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_019y2ew73NNyXuXKzJW6edQ8"}}
