{"ts": "2026-04-03T23:57:36.140", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Agent", "tool_input": {"description": "Design auto-commit hook plan", "prompt": "Design an implementation plan for an async auto-commit hook that fires after TaskCompleted events.\n\n## Requirements\n1. Create a new async hook script that runs after each TaskCompleted event\n2. The hook should check `git status` for unstaged/untracked files\n3. Save the file list to a commit batch state file (separate from the workflow state.json)\n4. Run a headless Claude (`claude -p`) to generate a commit message for the batched files\n5. Commit the files using subprocess from the hook script\n6. Must be async (non-blocking) so it doesn't slow down the main Claude session\n\n## Existing Architecture\n\n### Hook Registration\nHooks are registered in `.claude/settings.local.json` under the `hooks` key. TaskCompleted already has an existing sync hook:\n```json\n\"TaskCompleted\": [\n  {\n    \"hooks\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"\\\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\\\"/.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/task_completed.py\",\n        \"timeout\": 30\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\nWe need to ADD a second async hook entry alongside this existing one.\n\n### Hook Patterns\n- All hooks are Python scripts in `.claude/hooks/workflow/`\n- Dispatchers are in `.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/`\n- State management uses `StateStore` class in `state_store.py` with file locking\n- `Hook` class in `hook.py` provides stdin reading and output methods\n- Config constants in `config/__init__.py`\n- Hooks read JSON from stdin with fields like: session_id, transcript_path, cwd, hook_event_name, task_id, task_subject\n\n### Async Hook Behavior (from docs)\n- Set `\"async\": true` on the hook config\n- Async hooks cannot block Claude's behavior\n- Hook receives same JSON input on stdin\n- Output delivered on next conversation turn via systemMessage/additionalContext\n- Each execution creates a separate background process\n\n### Headless Claude Usage\n```bash\nclaude -p \"prompt here\" --allowedTools \"Read,Edit,Bash\" --output-format json\n```\n- Use `--bare` for faster startup (skips hooks, MCP, etc.)\n- Can use `--allowedTools` to auto-approve tools\n\n## Design Considerations\n1. The script should use a SEPARATE state file (e.g., `commit_batch.json`) to avoid conflicts with the main workflow `state.json`\n2. Need a lock mechanism to prevent concurrent headless Claude instances from racing\n3. The headless Claude should be invoked with `--bare` to avoid triggering hooks recursively\n4. The commit message should reference the task subject from the hook input\n5. Need to handle the case where there are no unstaged files (no-op)\n6. Should only commit files in the project directory, not system files\n7. Should exclude files like `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.json`, `*.pyc`, etc.\n\n## Key Files\n- `.claude/settings.local.json` - Hook registration\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/task_completed.py` - Existing TaskCompleted dispatcher\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/hook.py` - Hook utilities\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/state_store.py` - State management with file locking\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/logger.py` - Logging\n\nPlease design a detailed implementation plan for this feature.", "subagent_type": "Plan"}, "tool_response": {"status": "completed", "prompt": "Design an implementation plan for an async auto-commit hook that fires after TaskCompleted events.\n\n## Requirements\n1. Create a new async hook script that runs after each TaskCompleted event\n2. The hook should check `git status` for unstaged/untracked files\n3. Save the file list to a commit batch state file (separate from the workflow state.json)\n4. Run a headless Claude (`claude -p`) to generate a commit message for the batched files\n5. Commit the files using subprocess from the hook script\n6. Must be async (non-blocking) so it doesn't slow down the main Claude session\n\n## Existing Architecture\n\n### Hook Registration\nHooks are registered in `.claude/settings.local.json` under the `hooks` key. TaskCompleted already has an existing sync hook:\n```json\n\"TaskCompleted\": [\n  {\n    \"hooks\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"\\\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\\\"/.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/task_completed.py\",\n        \"timeout\": 30\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\nWe need to ADD a second async hook entry alongside this existing one.\n\n### Hook Patterns\n- All hooks are Python scripts in `.claude/hooks/workflow/`\n- Dispatchers are in `.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/`\n- State management uses `StateStore` class in `state_store.py` with file locking\n- `Hook` class in `hook.py` provides stdin reading and output methods\n- Config constants in `config/__init__.py`\n- Hooks read JSON from stdin with fields like: session_id, transcript_path, cwd, hook_event_name, task_id, task_subject\n\n### Async Hook Behavior (from docs)\n- Set `\"async\": true` on the hook config\n- Async hooks cannot block Claude's behavior\n- Hook receives same JSON input on stdin\n- Output delivered on next conversation turn via systemMessage/additionalContext\n- Each execution creates a separate background process\n\n### Headless Claude Usage\n```bash\nclaude -p \"prompt here\" --allowedTools \"Read,Edit,Bash\" --output-format json\n```\n- Use `--bare` for faster startup (skips hooks, MCP, etc.)\n- Can use `--allowedTools` to auto-approve tools\n\n## Design Considerations\n1. The script should use a SEPARATE state file (e.g., `commit_batch.json`) to avoid conflicts with the main workflow `state.json`\n2. Need a lock mechanism to prevent concurrent headless Claude instances from racing\n3. The headless Claude should be invoked with `--bare` to avoid triggering hooks recursively\n4. The commit message should reference the task subject from the hook input\n5. Need to handle the case where there are no unstaged files (no-op)\n6. Should only commit files in the project directory, not system files\n7. Should exclude files like `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.json`, `*.pyc`, etc.\n\n## Key Files\n- `.claude/settings.local.json` - Hook registration\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/task_completed.py` - Existing TaskCompleted dispatcher\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/hook.py` - Hook utilities\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/state_store.py` - State management with file locking\n- `.claude/hooks/workflow/logger.py` - Logging\n\nPlease design a detailed implementation plan for this feature.", "agentId": "a9f520d97ccfaac35", "agentType": "Plan", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I have all the information needed. Here is the complete implementation plan.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan: Async Auto-Commit Hook on TaskCompleted\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\nThe auto-commit hook is a standalone async Python script registered as a second hook entry under `TaskCompleted` in `settings.local.json`. It runs in a background process (via Claude's `\"async\": true` mechanism), so it never blocks the main session. It uses its own state file (`commit_batch.json`) and lock file to avoid conflicts with the main workflow state.\n\n### File Inventory\n\n| File | Action | Purpose |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `.claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py` | **Create** | Main async hook script |\n| `.claude/hooks/workflow/commit_batch.json` | **Created at runtime** | Batch state for pending commits |\n| `.claude/hooks/workflow/config/paths.py` | **Modify** | Add `COMMIT_BATCH_PATH` constant |\n| `.claude/settings.local.json` | **Modify** | Register the async hook |\n\n### Step-by-Step Implementation\n\n---\n\n#### Step 1: Add path constant to config\n\n**File:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/config/paths.py`\n\nAdd a new constant:\n\n```python\nCOMMIT_BATCH_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"commit_batch.json\"\n```\n\nAlso export it from `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/config/__init__.py` by adding `COMMIT_BATCH_PATH` to the imports from `workflow.config.paths`.\n\n---\n\n#### Step 2: Create the auto-commit hook script\n\n**File:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py`\n\nThis is the core implementation. The script should be executable (`chmod +x`).\n\n**Structure:**\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"auto_commit.py \u2014 Async auto-commit hook for TaskCompleted events.\n\nRuns as an async hook (non-blocking). On each TaskCompleted:\n1. Checks git status for unstaged/untracked files\n2. Saves file list to commit_batch.json\n3. Invokes headless Claude (--bare) to generate a commit message\n4. Commits the files via subprocess\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom filelock import FileLock\n\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent))\n\nfrom workflow.hook import Hook\nfrom workflow.logger import log\nfrom workflow.config.paths import WORKFLOW_ROOT\n\nCOMMIT_BATCH_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"commit_batch.json\"\nCOMMIT_LOCK_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"locks\" / \"auto_commit.lock\"\nPROJECT_DIR = Path.cwd()\n\n# Files/patterns to exclude from auto-commit\nEXCLUDE_PATTERNS = [\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/state.json\",\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/state.lock\",\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/commit_batch.json\",\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/commit_batch.lock\",\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/workflow.log\",\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/locks/\",\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/__pycache__/\",\n    \".claude/hooks/workflow/pytest-of-emhar/\",\n    \".claude/settings.local.json\",\n    \"*.pyc\",\n    \"__pycache__\",\n]\n```\n\n**Key functions to implement:**\n\n1. **`get_dirty_files() -> list[str]`** -- Run `git status --porcelain` and parse the output. Filter out files matching `EXCLUDE_PATTERNS`. Return list of relative paths. If empty, return empty list (no-op).\n\n2. **`save_batch(files: list[str], task_subject: str) -> None`** -- Use `StateStore` (or direct `FileManager`) to write to `commit_batch.json` with structure:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"files\": [\"path/to/file1.py\", \"path/to/file2.ts\"],\n     \"task_subject\": \"Implement feature X\",\n     \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-03T12:00:00.000\",\n     \"status\": \"pending\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **`generate_commit_message(files: list[str], task_subject: str) -> str`** -- Invoke headless Claude with `--bare` to avoid recursive hook triggers. The command should be:\n   ```python\n   prompt = f\"\"\"Generate a concise git commit message for the following changes.\n   Task: {task_subject}\n   Files changed:\n   {chr(10).join(f'- {f}' for f in files)}\n   \n   Respond with ONLY the commit message, no explanation. Use conventional commit format.\n   Keep the first line under 72 characters. Add a blank line then a body if needed.\"\"\"\n   \n   result = subprocess.run(\n       [\"claude\", \"--bare\", \"-p\", prompt],\n       capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=60\n   )\n   return result.stdout.strip()\n   ```\n   Important: use `--bare` flag so the headless instance skips hooks entirely, preventing infinite recursion. Use `-p` for non-interactive print mode. Do NOT use `--tools` or `--allowedTools` since this is a pure text generation task (no tool use needed).\n\n4. **`commit_files(files: list[str], message: str) -> bool`** -- Stage and commit:\n   ```python\n   subprocess.run([\"git\", \"add\"] + files, check=True)\n   subprocess.run([\"git\", \"commit\", \"-m\", message], check=True)\n   ```\n\n5. **`main()`** -- Orchestrate the flow:\n   ```python\n   def main():\n       raw_input = Hook.read_stdin()\n       task_subject = raw_input.get(\"task_subject\", \"Unknown task\")\n       \n       lock = FileLock(str(COMMIT_LOCK_PATH), timeout=10)\n       try:\n           with lock:\n               files = get_dirty_files()\n               if not files:\n                   log(\"AutoCommit:skip\", reason=\"no dirty files\")\n                   return\n               \n               save_batch(files, task_subject)\n               log(\"AutoCommit:generating\", file_count=len(files))\n               \n               message = generate_commit_message(files, task_subject)\n               if not message:\n                   message = f\"chore: auto-commit after task ({task_subject})\"\n               \n               commit_files(files, message)\n               \n               # Update batch state\n               update_batch_status(\"committed\", message)\n               log(\"AutoCommit:committed\", message=message, file_count=len(files))\n               \n               # Report back via async hook output\n               Hook.system_message(\n                   f\"Auto-committed {len(files)} file(s): {message}\"\n               )\n       except Timeout:\n           log(\"AutoCommit:lock_timeout\", reason=\"another auto-commit in progress\")\n       except Exception as e:\n           log(\"AutoCommit:error\", error=str(e))\n   ```\n\n**Critical design decisions in this script:**\n\n- **FileLock with timeout=10**: If another async auto-commit is already running (e.g., from a rapid sequence of TaskCompleted events), the lock prevents racing. A 10-second timeout means it will give up rather than block indefinitely.\n- **`--bare` flag on headless Claude**: This is essential to prevent the headless Claude instance from triggering hooks itself, which would cause infinite recursion (the auto-commit hook fires on TaskCompleted, which could fire again).\n- **No `-p` prompt for tool use**: The headless Claude only needs to generate text (a commit message), so no tools are needed. This makes it faster and safer.\n- **`EXCLUDE_PATTERNS`**: Prevents committing workflow state files, lock files, logs, and compiled Python files that should not be versioned.\n\n---\n\n#### Step 3: Register the async hook in settings\n\n**File:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/settings.local.json`\n\nModify the `TaskCompleted` array to add a second entry with `\"async\": true`. The existing sync hook remains unchanged at index 0. Add a new entry at index 1:\n\n```json\n\"TaskCompleted\": [\n  {\n    \"hooks\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"\\\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\\\"/.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/task_completed.py\",\n        \"timeout\": 30\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"hooks\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"\\\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\\\"/.claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py\",\n        \"timeout\": 120,\n        \"async\": true\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\n\nKey points:\n- `\"timeout\": 120` -- headless Claude can take 30-60 seconds, plus git operations. 120 seconds is generous but safe.\n- `\"async\": true` -- makes this non-blocking. The main session continues immediately.\n- The output (from `Hook.system_message`) will be delivered on the next conversation turn as a `systemMessage`.\n\n---\n\n#### Step 4: Create the lock file directory entry\n\nThe lock file `auto_commit.lock` will be created automatically by `filelock` in the existing `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/locks/` directory (which already exists and contains `state.lock`).\n\n---\n\n### Edge Cases and Error Handling\n\n1. **No dirty files**: `get_dirty_files()` returns empty list, script exits immediately with a log entry. No commit, no headless Claude invocation.\n\n2. **Headless Claude fails or times out**: Fall back to a templated commit message like `chore: auto-commit after task ({task_subject})`. Log the error but do not fail the hook.\n\n3. **Concurrent auto-commits**: The `FileLock` on `auto_commit.lock` with `timeout=10` prevents two async hook instances from racing. If the lock times out, the second instance logs and exits gracefully.\n\n4. **Git commit fails** (e.g., nothing to commit after staging): Catch `subprocess.CalledProcessError`, log the error, and exit. Do not propagate the error since async hooks cannot block Claude anyway.\n\n5. **Recursive hook prevention**: The `--bare` flag on the headless Claude instance ensures it does not load hooks. Without this, the headless instance completing a task could trigger another auto-commit, creating an infinite loop.\n\n6. **Files outside project directory**: `git status --porcelain` only reports files within the repo, so this is inherently handled. The `EXCLUDE_PATTERNS` filter handles workflow-internal files.\n\n### Execution Flow Diagram\n\n```\nTaskCompleted event fires\n    |\n    +---> [sync] task_completed.py (existing guardrail dispatcher)\n    |         runs guardrail check, blocks or allows\n    |\n    +---> [async] auto_commit.py (new, non-blocking)\n              |\n              +-- Read stdin JSON (task_subject, session_id, etc.)\n              +-- Acquire FileLock(auto_commit.lock, timeout=10)\n              +-- git status --porcelain\n              +-- Filter out excluded patterns\n              +-- If no files: log skip, exit\n              +-- Save to commit_batch.json\n              +-- claude --bare -p \"generate commit message...\"\n              +-- git add <files>\n              +-- git commit -m \"<generated message>\"\n              +-- Update commit_batch.json status\n              +-- Log success\n              +-- Output systemMessage (delivered next turn)\n              +-- Release lock\n```\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\n1. **Unit test `get_dirty_files()`**: Mock `subprocess.run` for `git status --porcelain` and verify filtering logic.\n2. **Unit test `generate_commit_message()`**: Mock the headless Claude subprocess call, verify prompt construction and fallback behavior.\n3. **Integration test**: Create a temp git repo, make changes, run the hook with mock stdin, verify commit was made with expected message.\n4. **Lock contention test**: Run two instances simultaneously and verify only one commits while the other exits gracefully.\n\n---\n\n### Critical Files for Implementation\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py` (new file, core implementation)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/settings.local.json` (add async hook registration)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/config/paths.py` (add COMMIT_BATCH_PATH constant)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/config/__init__.py` (export new constant)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/headless_claude/claude.py` (reference for headless Claude patterns)"}], "totalDurationMs": 118548, "totalTokens": 28944, "totalToolUseCount": 23, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 217, "cache_read_input_tokens": 25589, "output_tokens": 3137, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 217}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01PhxCrbNdh1oD15ScAGLv14"}}
